31 under this section is the percentage of the sponsor school corporation.
32 (c) Except as provided in subsection (d), the complexity index for
33 a school corporation that has entered into an agreement with one (1) or
34 more charter schools to participate as an innovation network charter
35 school under IC 20-25.7-5 for a state fiscal year is equal to the result
36 using the following formula:
37 STEP ONE: Determine:
38 (A) the school corporation's enrollment; minus
39 (B) the enrollment of students described in
40 IC 20-25.7-5-2(b)(2) of each participating innovation network
41 charter school.
42 STEP TWO: Determine the number of students in the school
2026 IN 1176—LS 6675/DI 110

12
1 corporation who were receiving Supplemental Nutrition
2 Assistance Program (SNAP) benefits, Temporary Assistance for
3 Needy Families (TANF) benefits, or foster care services as of
4 October 1 in the school year ending in 2025, not including
5 students enrolled in each participating innovation network charter
6 school.
7 STEP THREE: Divide the result of STEP TWO by the result of
8 STEP ONE.
9 STEP FOUR: Determine the enrollment of students described in
10 IC 20-25.7-5-2(b)(2) of each participating innovation network
11 charter school.
12 STEP FIVE: Determine the number of students described in
13 IC 20-25.7-5-2(b)(2) in each participating innovation network
14 charter school who were receiving Supplemental Nutrition
15 Assistance Program (SNAP) benefits, Temporary Assistance for
16 Needy Families (TANF) benefits, or foster care services as of
17 October 1 in the school year ending in the later of:
18 (A) 2025; or
19 (B) the first year of operation of the participating innovation
20 network charter school.
21 STEP SIX: Divide the result of STEP FIVE by the result of STEP
22 FOUR.
23 STEP SEVEN: For each participating innovation network charter
24 school, determine the greater of:
25 (A) the result of STEP THREE; or
26 (B) the result of STEP SIX.
27 STEP EIGHT: For each participating innovation network charter
28 school, multiply the result of STEP SEVEN by the result of STEP
29 FOUR.
30 STEP NINE: Determine the sum of:
31 (A) the result of STEP TWO; plus
32 (B) the results of STEP EIGHT, for each participating
33 innovation network charter school.
34 STEP TEN: Determine the sum of:
35 (A) the result of STEP ONE; plus
36 (B) the results of STEP FOUR for each participating
37 innovation network charter school.
38 STEP ELEVEN: Divide the STEP NINE result by the STEP TEN
39 result.
