29 (3) money in the ESA account when the ESA account is
30 terminated reverts does not revert to the state general fund and
31 remains available to provide grants to eligible students under
32 this chapter;
33 (4) the parent of the eligible student or the emancipated eligible
34 student will use part of the money in the ESA account:
35 (A) for the eligible student's study in the subject of reading,
36 grammar, mathematics, social studies, or science; or
37 (B) for use in accordance with the eligible student's:
38 (i) individualized education program;
39 (ii) service plan developed under 511 IAC 7-34;
40 (iii) choice special education plan developed under 511
41 IAC 7-49; or
42 (iv) plan developed under Section 504 of the federal
2026 IN 1176—LS 6675/DI 110

14
1 Rehabilitation Act of 1973, 29 U.S.C. 794;
2 (5) the eligible student will not be enrolled in a school that
3 receives tuition support under IC 20-43; and
4 (6) the eligible student will take the statewide summative
5 assessment, as applicable based on the eligible student's grade
6 level, as provided under IC 20-32-5.1, or the assessment specified
7 in the eligible student's:
8 (A) individualized education program developed under
9 IC 20-35;
10 (B) service plan developed under 511 IAC 7-34;
11 (C) choice special education plan developed under 511
12 IAC 7-49; or
13 (D) plan developed under Section 504 of the federal
14 Rehabilitation Act of 1973, 29 U.S.C. 794.
15 (b) A parent of an eligible student may enter into a separate
16 agreement under subsection (a) for each child of the parent. However,
17 not more than one (1) ESA account may be established for each
18 eligible student.
19 (c) The ESA account must be established under subsection (a) by a
20 parent of an eligible student or an emancipated eligible student for a
21 school year on or before a date established by the department which
22 must be at least thirty (30) days before the fall count day of ADM
23 established under IC 20-43-4-3. A parent of an eligible student or an
24 emancipated eligible student may not enter into an agreement under
25 this section or maintain an ESA account under this chapter if the
26 eligible student receives a choice scholarship under IC 20-51-4 for the
27 same school year. An eligible student may not receive a grant under
28 section 2 of this chapter if the eligible student is currently included in
29 a school corporation's ADM count under IC 20-43-4.
30 (d) Except as provided in subsections (e) and (f), an agreement
31 made under this section is valid for one (1) school year while the
32 eligible student is in kindergarten through grade 12 and may be
33 renewed annually. Upon graduation, or receipt of a certificate of
34 completion under the eligible student's individualized education
35 program, the eligible student's ESA account is terminated.
36 (e) An agreement entered into under this section terminates
37 automatically for an eligible student if:
38 (1) the eligible student no longer resides in Indiana while the
39 eligible student is eligible to receive grants under section 2 of this
40 chapter; or
41 (2) the ESA account is not renewed within three hundred
42 ninety-five (395) days after the date the ESA account was either
2026 IN 1176—LS 6675/DI 110

15
1 established or last renewed.
2 If an ESA account is terminated under this section, money in the
3 eligible student's ESA account, including any interest accrued, reverts
4 does not revert to the state general fund and remains available to
5 provide grants to eligible students under this chapter.
6 (f) An agreement made under this section for an eligible student
7 while the eligible student is in kindergarten through grade 12 may be
8 terminated before the end of the school year if the parent of the eligible
9 student or the emancipated eligible student notifies the department in
10 a manner specified by the department.
11 (g) A distribution made to an ESA account under section 2 of this
12 chapter is considered tax exempt as long as the distribution is used for
13 an ESA qualified expense. The amount is subtracted from the
14 definition of adjusted federal gross income under IC 6-3-1-3.5 to the
15 extent the distribution used for the ESA qualified expense is included
16 in the taxpayer's adjusted federal gross income under the Internal
17 Revenue Code.
18 (h) The department shall establish a student test number as
19 described in IC 20-19-3-9.4 for each eligible student.
20 (i) A student described in IC 20-51.4-2-4(3)(B) may not use the
21 money deposited into the eligible student's ESA account for ESA
22 qualified expenses described in IC 20-51.4-2-9(a)(3),
23 IC 20-51.4-2-9(a)(6), IC 20-51.4-2-9(a)(7), or IC 20-51.4-2-9(a)(9).
24 SECTION 10. IC 20-51.4-4-2, AS AMENDED BY P.L.213-2025,
