26 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 2. (a) An eligible student who
27 currently maintains an ESA account is entitled to an ESA annual grant
28 amount for each school year until the student graduates or obtains a
29 certificate of completion under the student's individualized education
30 program. An eligible student may not receive a grant under this section
31 after graduating or obtaining a certificate of completion. The ESA
32 annual grant amount shall be paid from the ESA program fund. The
33 department shall deposit the ESA annual grant amount under this
34 section, in quarterly deposits, into an eligible student's ESA account.
35 (b) Except as provided in subsection (c), at the end of the year in
36 which an ESA account is established, the parent of an eligible student
37 or the emancipated eligible student may roll over for use in a
38 subsequent year a maximum of one thousand dollars ($1,000).
