4 SECTION 220, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS
5 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 1. (a) After June 30, 2023, a parent
6 of a career scholarship student or an emancipated career scholarship
7 student may establish a career scholarship account for the career
8 scholarship student by entering into a written agreement with the
9 department on a form prepared by the department. An application to
10 establish a CSA account, or an application to participate in the CSA
11 program with an ESA account, must be submitted not later than
12 October 1 for the school year. Subject to subsection (f), the CSA
13 account of a career scholarship student must be made in the name of
14 the career scholarship student. The department shall make the
15 agreement available on the website of the department.
16 (b) To be eligible to participate in the CSA program, a parent of a
17 career scholarship student or an emancipated career scholarship student
18 must agree that:
19 (1) a grant deposited in the career scholarship student's CSA
20 account under section 3 of this chapter and any interest that may
21 accrue in the CSA account will be used only for the CSA
22 qualified expenses;
23 (2) money in the CSA account when the CSA account is
24 terminated reverts does not revert to the state general fund and
25 remains available to provide grants to career scholarship
26 students under this chapter; and
27 (3) the parent of the career scholarship student or the emancipated
28 career scholarship student will use the money in the CSA account
29 for the career scholarship student to attend one (1) or more of the
30 sequences, courses, apprenticeships, or programs of study
31 designated and approved under section 6(a) of this chapter.
32 (c) A parent of a career scholarship student may enter into a
33 separate agreement under subsection (a) for each child of the parent.
34 However, not more than one (1) CSA account may be established for
35 each career scholarship student.
36 (d) Except as provided under subsection (f), a CSA account must be
37 established under subsection (a) by a parent of a career scholarship
38 student or an emancipated career scholarship student for a school year
39 not later than thirty (30) days after the date that the department
40 approves an application submitted under subsection (a).
41 (e) Except as provided in section 2 of this chapter, an agreement
42 made under this section is valid for one (1) school year while the career
